  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will compare 3 dimensional intracardiac echo (ICE) with 2 dimensional ICE or
      transesophageal echo in patients with structural and valvular heart disease who are already
      scheduled to undergo a percutaneous intervention. Specifically those patients would be those
      scheduled for a PFO or ASD repair, mitral balloon valvuloplasty, diagnostic cardiac
      catheterization assessment of aortic stenosis and those undergoing transcatheter aortic valve
      replacement.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
